Research by MyBroadband shows that MTN has the best mobile network in South Africa, and reigns supreme in Gauteng, Cape Town, and Durban. This was revealed in MyBroadband’s Q1 2018 Mobile Network Quality Report. The report is based on 142,537 speed tests which were performed by thousands of MyBroadband Android Speed Test app users across South Africa between 1 January 2018 and 31 March 2018. It also shows that South Africa had an average mobile download speed of 20.03Mbps during the period. MTN had the highest average download speed at 24.12Mbps, followed by Vodacom on 21.26Mbps, Cell C on 15.95Mbps, and Telkom on 15.20Mbps. To determine the best mobile network in South Africa, a “Network Quality Score” was calculated for each network using a range of performance measurements. The Network Quality Score out of 10 shows how the network performed in relation to other networks. MTN won with a Network Quality Score of 9.92, followed by Vodacom on 9.01, Cell C on 6.72, and Telkom on 6.54.  MTN has the best network in Gauteng with a Network Quality Score of 9.99, followed by Vodacom on 9.34, Cell C on 7.37, and Telkom on 6.18.  MTN has the best network in Cape Town with a Network Quality Score of 9.59, followed by Vodacom on 8.86, Telkom on 6.11, and Cell C on 5.82.  MTN has the best network in Durban with a Network Quality Score of 9.93, followed by Vodacom on 6.77, Cell C on 5.98, and Telkom on 5.29. 